T1  - The intercountry agricultural production function and productivity differences among countries: Comment
AU  - Moll, Peter
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 28
IS  - 1
SP  - 121
EP  - 124
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/02/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(88)90018-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387888900181
AB  - Kawagoe, Hayami and Ruttan (1985) find, using an intercountry agricultural production function, that scale economies explain 15% of the difference in labour productivity between developed and less developed countries. In this note their finding of large scale economies in developed countries is contrasted with the commoner finding of approximately constant returns to scale in studies using farm-level data, and is likened to other studies employing grouped data, which also find large scale economies. It is suggested that the latter finding may be due to statistical artefact arising from the grouped nature of the data.
ER  - 
